WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:03.961
NARRATOR:
In a land of myth...

00:04.129 --> 00:05.714
...and a time of magic...

00:05.881 --> 00:07.674
...the destiny of a great kingdom...

00:07.841 --> 00:10.969
...rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:11.136 --> 00:15.140
His name, Merlin.

00:24.733 --> 00:26.985
[ALL SHOUTING]

00:36.119 --> 00:37.788
MAN:
Get him!

00:41.291 --> 00:43.126
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

01:03.146 --> 01:06.650
Trapped, are we?

01:07.276 --> 01:08.527
[WHOOSHING]

01:08.694 --> 01:10.028
[MAN GROANS]

01:16.493 --> 01:18.036
That's the idea.

01:19.288 --> 01:20.706
ARTHUR:
On me!

01:56.325 --> 01:59.494
Your Majesty! Look what we have here.

01:59.661 --> 02:02.414
He comes with us. I'll deal with the prisoners
when we get to Camelot.

02:02.581 --> 02:04.791
| fear this is no ordinary prisoner,
Your Highness.

02:13.550 --> 02:15.093
Well, well.

02:15.260 --> 02:16.803
What is it?

02:16.970 --> 02:20.557
This, Merlin, is the royal crest of Caerleon.

02:20.724 --> 02:22.601
Is it not...

02:24.269 --> 02:26.063
...Your Highness?

02:28.190 --> 02:30.484
This is not the first time
he's trespassed on our lands.

02:30.651 --> 02:34.404
No, sire. Only last week, he seized the village
of Stonedown on the western borders.

02:34.571 --> 02:36.406
We're not on the borders now, Agravaine.

02:36.573 --> 02:39.660
This is the heart of the kingdom.
He took a grave risk coming here.

02:39.826 --> 02:42.245
Perhaps he doesn't see it that way.

02:43.997 --> 02:48.043
| fear it's no coincidence that all this
has happened since Uther's death.

02:48.752 --> 02:50.128
What do you mean?

02:50.754 --> 02:53.965
Arthur, your father was a strong king.

02:54.132 --> 02:56.551
His enemies feared
and respected that strength.

02:56.718 --> 02:58.762
Are you saying I'm not worthy
of that respect?

02:58.929 --> 03:00.889
AGRAVAINE:
No, sire. Not at all.

03:01.056 --> 03:04.309
There isn't a citizen of Camelot
who would not lay down their life for you.

03:07.688 --> 03:11.650
But your enemies--
To the enemies of Camelot...

03:11.817 --> 03:15.070
...you are still untested as a king.

03:16.238 --> 03:18.115
You must send a clear message...

03:18.281 --> 03:21.702
...that any action against Camelot
will be met without mercy.

03:21.868 --> 03:23.870
Did we not achieve that here today?

03:24.371 --> 03:26.998
No, sire. Not enough.

03:27.165 --> 03:29.167
Not enough to deter the likes
of Odin and Ba yard...

03:29.334 --> 03:31.128
...and the others
who covet Camelot's wealth.

03:31.294 --> 03:32.963
Then what do you suggest?

03:34.631 --> 03:37.134
| suggest...

03:38.885 --> 03:43.014
| suggest that we force him to accept
a treaty on our terms.

03:43.640 --> 03:46.685
He must withdraw his men from our land.

03:47.310 --> 03:49.312
Return our territories to us.

03:50.439 --> 03:52.899
He must surrender Evorwick.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.235
He'd rather die than agree to such terms.

03:55.402 --> 03:57.738
Then you are left with no choice.

03:58.613 --> 04:00.782
| can't just kill a man in cold blood.

04:01.616 --> 04:04.870
Arthur, you must do what you need to do
to assert your authority on this land.

04:06.455 --> 04:07.581
There must be another way.

04:08.165 --> 04:10.083
There's no other way.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.379
Think on it.

04:16.464 --> 04:17.966
Decide by tomorrow.

04:28.268 --> 04:31.396
-Arthur.
-Not now, Merlin.

04:34.566 --> 04:36.109
[WATER SIZZLES]

04:47.454 --> 04:49.039
[GROANS]

04:51.208 --> 04:53.084
Arthur?

04:53.752 --> 04:55.212
Arthur.

04:56.338 --> 04:57.631
Here.

04:58.715 --> 05:00.050
Thank you.

05:00.217 --> 05:02.010
You must be cold.

05:05.847 --> 05:08.600
-Have you not slept at all?
-I've been thinking.

05:09.309 --> 05:11.019
About what Agravaine said?

05:14.189 --> 05:17.692
So, what are you going to do?

05:19.778 --> 05:21.363
My father was a great king...

05:22.155 --> 05:25.158
...but I don't have his wisdom
or his conviction.

05:25.325 --> 05:28.954
| can only follow his example
and do what he would have done.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.165
You're going to draw up this treaty?

05:33.667 --> 05:36.002
| have to show my strength.

05:36.336 --> 05:39.673
-Show that I'm worthy of my father's name.
-Caerleon won't sign it.

05:43.051 --> 05:46.346
-You know that.
-Caerleon brought this upon himself.

05:47.264 --> 05:48.849
Arthur.

05:49.182 --> 05:51.184
You've always shown mercy in battle.

05:51.351 --> 05:55.105
You've never sought to humiliate
your enemy in this way.

05:55.272 --> 05:57.482
This isn't like you. This isn't who you are.

05:57.649 --> 05:59.943
You have no idea what it is
to make these decisions.

06:00.110 --> 06:02.404
Decisions that will shape
the future of this land.

06:02.571 --> 06:07.075
-Arthur--
-So, please, stick to what you do know.

06:20.338 --> 06:22.132
What is this?

06:28.722 --> 06:31.433
You expect me to sign this?

06:32.475 --> 06:34.060
To humiliate myself before you?

06:34.227 --> 06:35.604
You invaded our kingdom...

06:36.271 --> 06:37.939
...took what did not belong to you.

06:38.106 --> 06:41.651
-And if I do not sign?
-Then you will pay with your life.

06:41.902 --> 06:43.445
[CHUCKLES]

06:43.612 --> 06:45.280
And who makes these terms?

06:45.447 --> 06:47.824
Arthur Pendragon...

06:49.117 --> 06:50.327
...king of Camelot.

06:55.040 --> 06:56.791
Very well.

07:05.008 --> 07:07.344
Then make it quick.

07:12.641 --> 07:14.476
Think what you're doing, Caerleon.

07:14.643 --> 07:16.853
This treaty could seal a truce between us.

07:17.020 --> 07:20.607
There would be peace,
like there was between your father and mine.

07:20.774 --> 07:22.651
| am not my father.

07:22.984 --> 07:24.778
And you are not Uther.

07:29.032 --> 07:31.326
Do you really have the guts to kill me?

07:33.578 --> 07:36.706
-You leave me no choice.
-You do not choose anything, boy.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.086
It is I who choose to die, and I alone.

07:43.088 --> 07:44.589
Now get on with it.

07:49.177 --> 07:51.054
So be it.

08:10.865 --> 08:15.328
Your resolve has already earned the respect
of both the council and the people alike.

08:15.495 --> 08:18.081
-Your father would have been proud of you.
-Thank you, uncle.

08:18.248 --> 08:22.085
| don't know what I'd have done
without your support and counsel.

08:33.054 --> 08:35.640
-Did you miss me?
-Yes, I did.

08:40.395 --> 08:42.772
It can't have been easy
having a man killed like that.

08:44.232 --> 08:47.485
| had no choice.
A show of strength was necessary.

08:49.404 --> 08:52.699
Don't you think compassion
can also show strength?

08:54.659 --> 08:57.454
Not to the likes of Caerleon. No.

08:57.787 --> 09:00.206
No, an example had to be made
for the good of the kingdom.

09:02.709 --> 09:04.919
So you don't regret what you did?

09:07.130 --> 09:09.966
My conscience is clean, Merlin,
which is more than I can say for my room.

09:10.133 --> 09:11.760
So just do your job, will you?

09:11.926 --> 09:15.764
Look, I'm just saying, if there's something
bothering you, you can talk to me.

09:15.930 --> 09:17.766
You shouldn't push your friends away,
you know.

09:17.932 --> 09:21.561
-Not now, not when you need them most.
-You're wrong, Merlin.

09:21.728 --> 09:24.981
| don't need anyone.
| can't afford that luxury.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.400
The kingdom's my responsibility now.

09:27.567 --> 09:29.402
Mine to bear alone.

09:30.487 --> 09:32.363
And you must learn to accept that.

09:59.808 --> 10:02.977
This-- This is no battle wound.

10:03.144 --> 10:05.939
This is the work of cowards!

10:08.483 --> 10:11.194
Arthur will pay for this, by God!

10:11.361 --> 10:14.864
The whole of Camelot will pay for this!

10:16.991 --> 10:18.493
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

10:18.660 --> 10:20.411
Come.

10:26.584 --> 10:28.002
| am sorry to disturb you, my lord.

10:28.169 --> 10:29.963
Is something the matter, uncle?

10:30.797 --> 10:34.050
| dare to hope that my advice...

10:34.217 --> 10:36.511
...has been of some use these past months.

10:36.678 --> 10:38.763
Of course it has. You know that.

10:39.180 --> 10:42.100
There is something I wish to discuss
with you.

10:42.267 --> 10:46.354
But it is a delicate matter.

10:48.648 --> 10:49.858
Yes?

10:50.817 --> 10:52.777
It concerns Gwynevere.

10:53.820 --> 10:55.071
What about her?

10:55.780 --> 10:57.657
She's a beautiful woman, sire...

10:57.824 --> 11:01.327
...and possessed of many fine qualities,
| have no doubt.

11:03.580 --> 11:06.040
But she is a servant.

11:06.833 --> 11:09.335
-That doesn't matter to me.
-Nor to me.

11:09.502 --> 11:12.547
| assure you. No.
It-- It's your people that concern me.

11:16.342 --> 11:19.137
Surely, as king, I can do as I see fit.

11:19.304 --> 11:22.599
No, sire. You cannot.

11:22.891 --> 11:24.475
You must do what is expected of you.

11:25.268 --> 11:28.813
You must present yourself
in an appropriate manner.

11:28.980 --> 11:31.941
The people-- Your people...

11:32.108 --> 11:34.402
...do not wish to see their king...

11:34.569 --> 11:36.863
...with the daughter of a blacksmith.

11:37.030 --> 11:39.073
This isn't a matter of state.

11:39.240 --> 11:41.284
This is a matter of the heart.

11:41.451 --> 11:43.953
You cannot rule the kingdom
with your heart, Arthur.

11:46.164 --> 11:48.416
Your father understood that.

11:56.007 --> 11:59.802
You didn't want to kill Caerleon. I know that.

12:00.428 --> 12:02.096
But you were strong.

12:02.263 --> 12:04.515
You didn't let those emotions
cloud your judgment.

12:04.682 --> 12:07.393
You ruled with your head,
like a strong king must.

12:09.771 --> 12:13.691
-Yes.
-Now you must show that strength again.

12:14.067 --> 12:19.697
Set aside personal feelings
for the good of your kingdom.

12:21.616 --> 12:23.701
Set aside my feelings for Gwynevere?

12:25.536 --> 12:27.789
I'm afraid so, my lord.

12:50.436 --> 12:53.064
-You seem tense.
-What do you mean, tense?

12:53.773 --> 12:57.777
You know. Agitated, on edge, angry.

12:57.944 --> 13:00.405
This is not anger, Merlin.

13:00.571 --> 13:02.991
This is controlled aggression!

13:05.285 --> 13:06.786
Great. I'm glad we cleared that up.

13:06.953 --> 13:09.539
Sire. A messenger this minute arrived.

13:09.706 --> 13:11.541
-What is it?
-An army.

13:11.708 --> 13:14.794
-It crossed our border at first light.
ARTHUR: An army? Whose army?

13:14.961 --> 13:17.088
Caerleon's queen.

13:21.426 --> 13:25.305
At a forced march, Caerleon's men will reach
Camelot by sundown tomorrow.

13:26.556 --> 13:28.599
Which means we have no choice.

13:28.766 --> 13:31.561
We must intercept them before they reach
the Ridge of Landshire.

13:31.728 --> 13:33.563
That way, we hold the high ground.

13:33.730 --> 13:36.149
The knights of Camelot
make ready as I speak.

13:37.317 --> 13:38.860
We ride at dawn.

13:39.736 --> 13:41.529
Long live the king!

13:41.696 --> 13:42.989
ALL:
Long live the king!

13:43.156 --> 13:47.076
Long live the king!
Long live the king!

13:54.792 --> 13:56.210
[ENERGY CRACKLES]

14:12.769 --> 14:14.270
GUARD:
Halt!

14:17.982 --> 14:21.736
Please, I mean you no harm.

14:24.322 --> 14:26.532
| wish only to speak with your queen.

14:37.043 --> 14:38.961
Morgana Pendragon.

14:39.128 --> 14:42.298
Stealing into my castle in the dead of night.

14:42.465 --> 14:44.133
You must have a death wish.

14:44.300 --> 14:47.261
Sorry for the interruption, Your Majesty,
but I've come on urgent business.

14:47.428 --> 14:50.890
What business could you possibly
have with me, witch?

14:51.057 --> 14:54.102
-I come in the name of my father.
-Is that so?

14:54.602 --> 14:56.896
When last I heard, you and he were--

14:57.063 --> 14:58.981
| speak not of Uther, but of Gorlois.

14:59.148 --> 15:02.735
-Gorlois?
-Uther is my father by blood alone.

15:02.902 --> 15:05.405
Gorlois raised me as a child.
He made me who I am.

15:05.571 --> 15:07.031
| remember him well.

15:07.198 --> 15:11.285
He was a good man, an honorable man.

15:11.452 --> 15:13.037
He was, Your Highness...

15:13.371 --> 15:16.416
...and his sole reward was death,
betrayed by his king.

15:17.708 --> 15:19.377
Well, then.

15:19.919 --> 15:24.048
It seems we have both lost something
at the hands of a Pendragon.

15:35.268 --> 15:37.812
Now, for the last time,
what are you doing here?

15:39.689 --> 15:41.399
Your Highness--

15:49.824 --> 15:53.953
Your Highness, Uther was a curse
upon this land, as is his son.

15:54.120 --> 15:58.416
| seek revenge for the wounds
they have inflicted, as do you.

16:01.169 --> 16:03.504
If you will accept it,
I've come to offer my help.

16:08.134 --> 16:09.552
Off again?

16:10.219 --> 16:12.513
Another week in the wilderness?

16:15.516 --> 16:19.520
Eating weird animals,
being eaten by weird animals.

16:19.687 --> 16:21.939
No hot water and no baths.

16:22.648 --> 16:25.985
This will be the last time either of us
get to sleep in a proper bed.

16:26.152 --> 16:28.488
I'm prepared to face all manner
of horrors in this world.

16:28.654 --> 16:31.657
-But if you think I'm sharing this bed with you--
-Ha-ha-ha.

16:31.824 --> 16:32.867
What?

16:33.034 --> 16:34.994
-No! That's not what I meant.
-Right.

16:35.161 --> 16:37.914
-Good. Comfort to know.
-Where are you going?

16:38.080 --> 16:42.668
That's my business. And, Merlin,
don't be here when I come back.

16:54.514 --> 16:57.391
GUARD:
Halt! Declare yourself!

17:01.062 --> 17:02.563
Sorry, sire. Forgive me.

17:03.231 --> 17:05.023
No harm done.

17:25.169 --> 17:26.878
-Arthur.
-May I come in?

17:27.046 --> 17:29.048
Of course.

17:30.508 --> 17:34.345
-Can I get you anything? Something to eat?
-I'm fine, thanks.

17:34.845 --> 17:37.390
- I won't be staying long.
-Oh.

17:41.394 --> 17:42.895
Gwynevere.

17:44.522 --> 17:47.525
Please believe me when I say
that you've done nothing wrong...

17:49.026 --> 17:53.030
...and that none of this
has anything to do with you.

17:53.197 --> 17:55.950
None of what? I don't understand.

17:57.868 --> 17:59.078
Things have changed for me.

18:00.663 --> 18:04.458
With my father gone,
it falls to me to rule this land.

18:04.625 --> 18:07.420
| know what a responsibility that must be.

18:08.087 --> 18:10.172
And now that I'm king...

18:12.425 --> 18:15.511
...it's no longer relevant what I may
or may not want for myself.

18:17.013 --> 18:20.558
My only duty is to the people of this land.

18:21.684 --> 18:25.146
I'll be judged by my actions,
who I'm seen with.

18:27.023 --> 18:29.567
-You're ashamed to be seen with me?
-No.

18:32.069 --> 18:33.529
No.

18:34.822 --> 18:37.867
But now that I'm king, it's not appropriate.

18:39.327 --> 18:41.579
I'm not appropriate?

18:45.166 --> 18:46.876
It seems not.

18:49.462 --> 18:51.130
Arthur.

18:51.672 --> 18:53.841
Listen to yourself.

18:54.592 --> 18:56.886
This doesn't sound like the man I know.

18:58.346 --> 19:02.183
-You've been talked into this, haven't you?
- Ihaven't been talked into anything.

19:03.184 --> 19:05.061
I'm my own man. I make my own decisions.

19:05.227 --> 19:08.397
And you've decided we can't be together?

19:12.485 --> 19:14.195
Yes.

19:15.946 --> 19:17.531
| see.

19:22.620 --> 19:24.747
I'm sorry, Gwynevere.

19:26.749 --> 19:28.584
It's just the way it has to be.

19:32.254 --> 19:33.923
Arthur.

19:34.757 --> 19:37.176
Don't let anyone tell you what to do.

19:38.260 --> 19:40.721
You said you are your own man.

19:41.806 --> 19:45.309
You have a good heart. Be true to it.

19:45.768 --> 19:48.688
Only then will you be the king
you want to be.

19:59.990 --> 20:01.534
[DOOR CLOSES]

20:24.807 --> 20:26.809
GAIUS:
Don't worry, Gwen.

20:27.226 --> 20:29.812
He'll be back soon, I'm sure.

20:30.813 --> 20:32.523
It's different this time though, isn't it?

20:34.233 --> 20:38.738
Arthur's king now. The fate of Camelot
rests on his shoulders alone.

20:39.071 --> 20:40.906
He's not alone, Gwen.

20:41.073 --> 20:43.701
You, above all people, should know that.

20:43.868 --> 20:45.953
| do know that.

20:46.120 --> 20:48.205
But I'm not sure he does.

21:05.765 --> 21:08.726
Ensure the men have everything they need.

21:09.435 --> 21:13.314
-They must be well rested by morning.
-I'll see to it, sire.

21:15.691 --> 21:17.359
The battle commences at first light.

21:25.743 --> 21:27.578
[MEN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

21:29.163 --> 21:31.248
[KNIGHTS CHATTERING]

21:34.168 --> 21:37.338
MERLIN: That's me.
ELYAN: Like a one-man army.

21:42.718 --> 21:44.428
[CHUCKLES]

21:53.229 --> 21:55.356
We should all get some sleep.

21:58.567 --> 22:00.402
Is he all right?

22:02.029 --> 22:03.739
He's our king.

22:03.906 --> 22:06.408
If anything were to happen to any of us...

22:06.575 --> 22:08.702
...he'll hold himself responsible.

22:22.299 --> 22:23.634
Elyan?

22:23.801 --> 22:25.261
Sire.

22:29.306 --> 22:30.599
Well?

22:30.766 --> 22:33.394
We just want you to know...

22:33.978 --> 22:37.189
...there isn't a man among us
who would not die for you.

22:37.690 --> 22:39.316
We made our pledge...

22:39.483 --> 22:42.111
...and we wear the Pendragon crest
with pride.

22:43.237 --> 22:46.532
Tomorrow we fight in your name, sire.

22:46.699 --> 22:50.578
For freedom and justice in this land.

22:53.330 --> 22:55.249
Thank you, Elyan.

22:56.333 --> 22:57.626
Thank you all.

23:13.100 --> 23:15.060
They mean it, sire.

23:15.477 --> 23:17.187
Every word.

23:18.397 --> 23:21.108
I've never once questioned their loyalty.

23:22.735 --> 23:24.987
| do wonder if I deserve it.

23:26.655 --> 23:28.991
No one could care more
for their men than you do.

23:29.158 --> 23:32.077
To send them into battle is not a decision
that you would make lightly.

23:32.244 --> 23:35.289
-They know that.
-But was it the right decision?

23:36.206 --> 23:39.668
If there was any other way out of this situation,
you would take it.

23:39.835 --> 23:41.545
But you must defend Camelot.

23:41.712 --> 23:43.839
-You have no choice.
- had a choice.

23:46.216 --> 23:48.552
To let Caerleon live or die.

23:51.931 --> 23:54.266
| made the wrong decision...

23:55.392 --> 23:58.395
...and now I've brought this war
upon Camelot myself.

23:59.897 --> 24:01.398
Arthur.

24:02.149 --> 24:05.736
No one is prepared to sacrifice
more for the sake of this kingdom than you.

24:05.903 --> 24:09.281
Your decision was made
in the best interests of Camelot.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.033
Maybe.

24:13.410 --> 24:16.538
Now my men must pay for it with their lives.

24:19.792 --> 24:21.794
[MAN SNORING]

25:13.095 --> 25:14.638
Halt!

25:21.603 --> 25:23.355
ARTHUR;:
I'm unarmed.

25:28.652 --> 25:30.571
You know who I am.

25:31.113 --> 25:33.032
Take me to your queen.

25:44.293 --> 25:46.837
-What is the meaning of this?
-Your Highness, I've come here to--

25:48.964 --> 25:51.884
Your Highness, I know that you feel nothing
but contempt for me.

25:52.760 --> 25:55.554
You feel I've done you a grievous wrong,
and you would be right.

25:55.721 --> 25:57.306
I'm ashamed of what I did.

25:57.473 --> 26:01.018
It was cowardly, it was unjust,
and I'm deeply sorry.

26:01.185 --> 26:03.854
Sorry does not bring back my husband.

26:04.021 --> 26:07.107
Sorry does not give my people back
their king.

26:07.274 --> 26:10.652
| realize that. I know there's nothing
| can do to repair that loss.

26:10.819 --> 26:13.447
Then what are you doing here,
Arthur Pendragon?

26:13.781 --> 26:15.991
| want to call off the battle.

26:17.284 --> 26:19.203
It's a little too late for that.

26:19.369 --> 26:21.997
| don't propose a truce, but an alternative.

26:22.748 --> 26:25.375
| invoke the right of single combat.

26:25.542 --> 26:27.669
Two champions
settle this matter between them.

26:28.837 --> 26:31.131
And why should I grant you this favor?

26:31.298 --> 26:33.217
There has been bloodshed enough,
Your Highness.

26:35.469 --> 26:37.805
Many hundreds of lives
will be saved this way.

26:42.768 --> 26:43.936
And your terms?

26:44.103 --> 26:46.146
If my man wins,
you must withdraw your army.

26:46.313 --> 26:48.565
And if mine is the victor?

26:49.191 --> 26:51.568
Then half of all Camelot is yours.

26:58.408 --> 26:59.660
[PANTING]

27:01.245 --> 27:03.122
-Sorry about this.
-You know him?

27:04.915 --> 27:08.001
He's my servant. He must have
followed me here. I knew nothing about it.

27:08.168 --> 27:10.796
-Kill him.
ARTHUR: Wait, please. Let him go.

27:10.963 --> 27:15.175
He's just a simple-minded fool.

27:18.011 --> 27:21.098
That is two favors...

27:21.265 --> 27:23.934
...you've asked of me this night,
Arthur Pendragon.

27:40.576 --> 27:44.246
Very well.
You shall have your trial by combat.

27:44.413 --> 27:47.499
Announce your champion
by noon tomorrow.

27:49.543 --> 27:51.086
Thank you, Your Highness.

27:51.253 --> 27:53.213
And take your fool with you.

28:00.387 --> 28:03.473
-Simple-minded fool?
-Oh, I was being kind. Believe me.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.184
-You almost got me killed in there.
-Me?

28:05.350 --> 28:07.269
You seem to be doing
a good job of that yourself.

28:07.436 --> 28:09.855
What is wrong with you?
Why can you never just leave me be?

28:10.022 --> 28:12.024
I'm your friend.

28:12.191 --> 28:13.609
| was looking out for you.

28:13.775 --> 28:16.862
| appreciate that in your very confused way...

28:17.029 --> 28:21.241
...you were only trying to help.
But please, don't do it again.

28:25.954 --> 28:27.873
But, sire, we can win this battle.
| know we can.

28:28.040 --> 28:31.835
| don't doubt it. But at what cost?
How many men would be slaughtered?

28:32.002 --> 28:35.964
And what if we were to lose this trial?
We can't give up our land.

28:36.131 --> 28:37.466
That's the deal I've struck.

28:38.217 --> 28:40.886
| believe it to be fair. I'll stand by it.

28:41.511 --> 28:45.641
Well, then all that remains, my lord,
is for you to choose your champion.

28:46.975 --> 28:49.102
- It would be a privilege, sire.
-Sire.

28:49.269 --> 28:51.355
There can only be one choice.

28:51.939 --> 28:55.234
One choice which is just and honorable.

28:56.068 --> 28:57.945
This fight's mine.

29:07.037 --> 29:10.123
| don't like it. It must be a trick.

29:10.874 --> 29:14.294
-What concerns you, Your Highness?
-Arthur.

29:14.461 --> 29:16.338
Why would he choose himself
as the champion?

29:16.838 --> 29:18.757
Because he's Arthur.

29:19.091 --> 29:22.135
He'll always risk his own life
before those of his men.

29:22.302 --> 29:25.931
Trust me, it's no trick. Arthur will fight.

29:26.098 --> 29:28.850
It's as if you were pleased, Morgana.

29:29.017 --> 29:31.687
Whatever else he is, Arthur is a great warrior.

29:31.853 --> 29:34.523
You have as much to lose as I if he wins.

29:35.565 --> 29:38.318
You desire the throne of Camelot,
do you not?

29:38.485 --> 29:41.071
| don't deny it. It's rightfully mine after all.

29:44.741 --> 29:46.868
Arthur will not win.

29:47.035 --> 29:49.162
How can you possibly know that?

29:50.872 --> 29:53.917
Because I have the power
to ensure that he doesn't.

29:57.838 --> 30:00.090
Then you must use it.

30:26.366 --> 30:28.285
[PANTING]

30:36.501 --> 30:37.961
Morgana.

30:38.962 --> 30:41.923
-Did you get it?
-Of course.

30:56.813 --> 30:59.483
[SPEAKING INCANTATION]

31:34.976 --> 31:37.270
Arthur's as good as dead.

31:44.569 --> 31:47.656
Not too tight, Merlin. You don't want to kill me
before I've even started.

31:47.823 --> 31:49.950
Heh. Sorry.

31:57.124 --> 32:01.545
If this day should prove to be my last,
give this to Gwynevere.

32:04.089 --> 32:05.966
Tell her I'm sorry.

32:07.217 --> 32:08.885
Of course.

32:12.639 --> 32:15.308
Arthur, do you really think this is worth
the risk? You're king now.

32:15.475 --> 32:17.727
Camelot needs you alive.

32:21.606 --> 32:23.191
| don't know what will happen.

32:24.818 --> 32:26.862
But for the first time since I became king...

32:27.988 --> 32:31.032
...know in my heart
I've made the right decision.

32:34.578 --> 32:38.790
Well, whatever happens out there, um--

32:40.959 --> 32:42.919
-You're not about to start crying are you?
-No.

32:43.086 --> 32:45.213
Just, uh, good luck.

32:45.922 --> 32:47.466
[LAUGHS]

32:49.050 --> 32:50.886
Thank you, old friend.

32:56.141 --> 32:58.185
It is time, my lord.

32:59.311 --> 33:00.854
Very well.

33:03.023 --> 33:04.441
Is all in readiness?

33:05.734 --> 33:07.486
Merlin?

33:09.488 --> 33:10.780
Ready.

33:24.044 --> 33:25.837
Right then.

33:45.482 --> 33:47.734
You have served my husband well, Derian.

33:48.735 --> 33:51.238
| know you'll do the same for me.

33:51.988 --> 33:53.657
And, Derian...

33:54.074 --> 33:56.409
...No pity, no quarter.

33:56.576 --> 33:58.620
Do not hesitate for one second.

33:58.787 --> 34:01.498
Arthur Pendragon must die.

34:58.763 --> 35:00.098
[GROWLS]

35:17.073 --> 35:18.283
[BOTH GRUNTING]

35:27.417 --> 35:28.710
[DERIAN ROARS]

36:01.159 --> 36:03.536
[YELLS]

36:09.626 --> 36:11.294
This has gone on long enough.

36:12.212 --> 36:13.963
Time to turn the tide.

36:14.130 --> 36:16.925
I've enchanted Arthur's sword.

36:17.258 --> 36:19.969
It holds the weight of a thousand ages.

36:20.345 --> 36:22.097
No one could bear it for long.

36:34.984 --> 36:36.236
[GROANS]

37:11.187 --> 37:12.230
[SPEAKS INCANTATION]

37:12.397 --> 37:13.815
[ROARS]

37:16.359 --> 37:18.611
[BOTH YELLING]

37:34.961 --> 37:37.547
[SOLDIERS CHEERING]

37:43.428 --> 37:45.388
Long live the king!

37:49.225 --> 37:51.394
SOLDIERS:
Long live the king!

38:09.329 --> 38:12.624
You are victorious, Arthur Pendragon.

38:15.794 --> 38:20.298
And you may rest assured that I shall comply
absolutely with the terms of our agreement.

38:21.382 --> 38:23.635
My army will be gone by nightfall.

38:23.802 --> 38:25.428
Thank you, Your Highness.

38:33.728 --> 38:38.733
Tell me something.
You spared my champion. Why?

38:38.900 --> 38:41.069
Because it's not victory I seek.

38:41.236 --> 38:43.112
It is peace.

38:44.531 --> 38:48.576
| hope that today will mark
a new beginning for our kingdoms.

38:50.954 --> 38:54.123
There is something about you,
Arthur Pendragon.

38:55.291 --> 38:58.628
Something which gives me hope for us all.

39:17.605 --> 39:20.483
It seems you do not have the power after all,
Morgana.

39:20.650 --> 39:23.278
Arthur was made of sterner stuff
than you imagined.

39:23.444 --> 39:25.029
[CHUCKLES]

39:25.488 --> 39:27.407
There will be other opportunities,
Your Highness.

39:27.574 --> 39:29.492
And next time he won't be so lucky.

39:29.659 --> 39:31.661
There won't be a next time.

39:33.121 --> 39:35.248
Not for me anyway.

39:35.415 --> 39:36.916
What are you talking about?

39:37.083 --> 39:40.169
| believe I may have misjudged
our young king.

39:40.336 --> 39:42.422
Don't be taken in by his fine words.

39:42.589 --> 39:45.216
It wasn't Arthur who mislead me. It was you.

39:47.051 --> 39:49.888
You are consumed by bitterness, Morgana.

39:50.054 --> 39:53.600
It spreads within you like a disease.

39:53.892 --> 39:57.061
In my grief, I let you infect me with your hate.

39:57.228 --> 39:58.980
That is untrue.

39:59.147 --> 40:01.232
Have you forgotten how
Arthur killed your husband?

40:01.900 --> 40:05.278
-Do you deny that you sought revenge?
-Yes, I sought revenge.

40:06.696 --> 40:09.699
But that does not mean
it was the right thing to do.

40:09.866 --> 40:11.242
[SCOFFS]

40:12.201 --> 40:14.329
You are weak, Annie...

40:14.495 --> 40:16.873
...as I thought you were.

40:17.498 --> 40:20.585
Go ahead. Make peace with Arthur.

40:20.752 --> 40:25.924
But I will not rest
until all of Camelot bows before me.

40:27.216 --> 40:29.052
Morgana.

40:30.178 --> 40:33.473
You came to me in the name of Gorlois...

40:33.932 --> 40:37.018
...but I fear you're more
like Uther than you realize.

40:51.824 --> 40:53.826
[ALL CHEERING]

41:03.211 --> 41:05.046
You're a hero.

41:05.421 --> 41:06.673
Thank you, Merlin.

41:06.839 --> 41:08.883
Not to me. To your people.

41:09.050 --> 41:12.345
Right. You think different?

41:13.096 --> 41:15.139
Maybe I know something they don't.

41:15.306 --> 41:16.975
Which is?

41:17.141 --> 41:20.687
You know, that you're a cabbage head.

41:21.854 --> 41:23.439
Maybe.

41:24.440 --> 41:26.484
| should have listened to you, Merlin.

41:26.651 --> 41:28.736
Just this once, I think you were right.

41:29.320 --> 41:31.990
Even if you are the worst servant
in the five kingdoms.

41:33.950 --> 41:35.743
[LAUGHS]

41:54.470 --> 41:56.347
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

41:57.223 --> 41:58.808
Come.

42:05.857 --> 42:08.359
-Gwen.
-Sire.

42:10.153 --> 42:11.863
These...

42:13.489 --> 42:15.324
...are for you.

42:18.578 --> 42:20.079
They're not much, I know.

42:20.246 --> 42:22.540
| picked them by the side of the road.

42:23.708 --> 42:26.419
Thank you, sire,
but I don't know what they're for.

42:28.046 --> 42:29.756
They're to say I'm sorry, Gwynevere.

42:31.591 --> 42:33.468
You don't need to apologize.

42:33.634 --> 42:36.137
| understand why things
have to be the way they are.

42:37.889 --> 42:41.517
Mm. A good king should...

42:41.684 --> 42:43.686
...respect the traditions of the past.

42:43.853 --> 42:46.606
-As my father did.
- I know that.

42:47.690 --> 42:50.401
But a good king should also...

42:50.568 --> 42:52.612
...be true to himself...

42:53.196 --> 42:55.698
...and do as he sees fit...

42:56.574 --> 43:00.119
...and be seen with those who he cares for.

43:02.997 --> 43:06.334
Even if they're not appropriate?

43:18.179 --> 43:20.056
Does that answer your question?

43:21.015 --> 43:22.934
It's a start.

43:37.532 --> 43:38.991
NARRATOR:
Merlin.

43:40.326 --> 43:42.578
MORGANA:
Arthur is strangely fond of the boy.

43:42.745 --> 43:44.205
He could prove useful.

43:44.372 --> 43:45.790
[GASPS]

43:45.957 --> 43:47.291
You must kill Arthur Pendragon.

43:49.043 --> 43:50.128
[HISSES]

43:50.294 --> 43:52.130
Merlin, is something wrong?

43:53.214 --> 43:55.049
But why would Merlin want to kill Arthur?

43:55.216 --> 43:59.887
You can't trust anyone. In fact, I think you,
Merlin, are the only person I can trust.

44:00.054 --> 44:01.597
You're just my imagination.

44:01.764 --> 44:03.099
Whatever you say.

44:47.185 --> 44:48.186
[English - US - SDH]
